original: AHXNER, Anders Harald, Civilingenjör, Direktör, Jönköping, f Mollösund, Gbgs o Boh l, 17/8 78 av sjökapt H O Andersson o Anna Andersson, gm Kerstin Johansson. CTL :s lägre avd 97—99, h avd 00—03 (maskinbyggn o mek tekn). Anst AB Eminent (AB Celcius) Gbg 03— 06, AB A Wiborghs Ing.byrå o Maskinaff 06— 10, start Värmeledn.fman Harald Ahxner 10, start fil i Jönkp 11, ombild huv.fman t AB Harald Ahxner, Sthlm, 34, lämnade AB Harald Ahxner våren 37, start Jönkps RörledningsAB våren 38. Utf värme- o sanitetstekn utredn samt installat av värme- o sanit anläggn i statl, kommun o priv anläggn, föret o bost.-hus mm. Led Sv Tekn.frn.
translated: AHXNER, Anders Harald, Civil Engineer, Director, Jönköping, b. Mollösund, Gothenburg and Bohus County, 17/8 1878, son of ship captain H O Andersson and Anna Andersson, m. Kerstin Johansson. Completed lower division of CTL (possibly a school or college) 97-99, higher division 00-03 (specializing in mechanical engineering and machine construction). Employed at AB Eminent (AB Celcius), Gothenburg, 03-06, AB A Wiborghs Engineering Office and Machine Trading 06-10. Started Harald Ahxner Heating Company 10, graduated with a degree in Philosophy in Jönköping 11, converted to CEO of AB Harald Ahxner, Stockholm, 34. Left AB Harald Ahxner spring 37, started Jönköping Pipeline AB spring 38. Carried out heating and sanitation engineering investigations and installations in state, municipal, and private buildings, commercial and residential houses, etc. Member of the Swedish Technical Association.
